  "text": "To conclude, there is still a need for an easy, fast, and truly specific assay with high precision and sensitivity. The consensus guidelines for assessing the specificity of CsA assays (4, 6 ) (slope to HPLC Յ10% from the line of identity; intercept Յ15 g/L, S y͉x Յ15 g/L) should be revised because they do not ensure sufficient specificity. It is necessary to demonstrate that there is no correlation between any observed bias and the individual content of metabolites in patients. Similar problems may be encountered in the monitoring of other drugs [e.g., Tacrolimus [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ].",
